```java
TextField textField = new TextField(&quot;123.456&quot;);
String s = textField.getText();
double value = s == null || s.isBlank() ? Double.NaN : Double.parseDouble(s.trim()); // 123.456
```

Since their is an exception while the String is not equal to a number, for example &quot;&quot; or &quot;hi&quot; you can just use
